'''Abdullah Ghanim Khawar''' is a 35-year-old notorious Qatari national and [[Qatar]]-based [[Qatar|terrorist financier]], who previously worked as a salesman.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.defenddemocracy.org/content/uploads/publications/Qatar_Part_I.pdf|title=Qatar and Terror Finance. Part I: Negligence|last=Weinberg|first=David Andrew|date=2014-12-01|website=www.defenddemocracy.org|publisher=Foundation for Defense of Democracies|access-date=2016-11-16}}</ref>

==Biography==
Khawar was born in [[Qatar]] on August 17, 1981.<ref>https://www.treasury.gov/resource-center/sanctions/OFAC-Enforcement/Pages/20110728.aspx</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://regulations.justia.com/regulations/fedreg/2011/08/03/2011-19643.html|title=Designation of Six Individuals Pursuant to Executive Order 13224, 46896-46897 [2011-19643]|last=|first=|date=|work=|newspaper=Justia Regulation Tracker|access-date=2016-11-16|via=}}</ref> According to the [[United States Department of the Treasury|U.S. Department of the Treasury]], he's obtained status as a U.S.-[[Al-Qaeda|designated al-Qaeda]] facilitator and financier in Qatar. He is closely linked with [[Salim al-Kuwari]], another U.S.-designated al-Qaeda financier who previously worked for Qatar's ministry of interior, with whom he worked with to deliver money, information, and other material support to al-Qaeda leaders in [[Iran]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.treasury.gov/press-center/press-releases/Pages/tg1261.aspx|title=Treasury Targets Key Al-Qa’ida Funding and Support Network Using Iran as a Critical Transit Point|website=www.treasury.gov|access-date=2016-11-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/11156327/Al-Qaeda-terror-financier-worked-for-Qatari-government.html|title=Al-Qaeda terror financier worked for Qatari government|newspaper=Telegraph.co.uk|access-date=2016-11-16}}</ref> Kuwari would donate would donate hundreds of thousands of dollars to al-Qaeda in Iran over the years using the assistance of Abdullah Ghanim Mafuz Muslim al-Khawar.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://formiche.net/2014/08/27/i-paesi-del-golfo-persico-che-finanziano-lisis/|title=Chi finanzia Isis. Stati, nomi e numeri|last=Sotgiu|first=Simona|date=2014-08-27|website=Formiche.net|access-date=2016-11-16}}</ref> He was responsible for moving money and recruits from the [[Persian Gulf|Gulf region]] to al-Qaeda leaders.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2011/07/treasury_targets_ira_1.php|title=Treasury targets Iran's ‘secret deal’ with al Qaeda|last=|first=|date=|website=The Long War Journal|publisher=|access-date=2016-11-16}}</ref> Khawar also played a large role in facilitating the travel and transport of al-Qaeda recruits to [[Afghanistan]], who are interested in taking part in [[jihad]] there.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://atfp.org/adopt/terrorist/abdallah-ghanim-mafuz-muslim-al-khawar/|title=Abdallah Ghanim Mafuz Muslim al-Khawar – Adopt a Terrorist for Prayer|last=|first=|date=|website=atfp.org|publisher=|access-date=2016-11-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.terrorfinanceblog.com/2014/06/al-qaeda-financiers-use-qatar-for-international-activities.html|title=Al Qaeda financiers use Qatar for international activities|last=|first=|date=|website=www.terrorfinanceblog.com|publisher=|access-date=2016-11-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://moneyjihad.wordpress.com/2014/06/30/5-qataris-who-fund-al-qaeda/|title=5 Qataris who fund Al Qaeda|date=2014-06-30|website=Money Jihad|access-date=2016-11-16}}</ref>

According to other renowned terrorist financier [[Abd Al-Rahman al-Nuaimi|Abd al-Rahman al-Nuayami's]] [[Alkarama]], the human rights organization that was a used as front for coordinating terrorist activities and funding, that Khawar was arrested along with Kuwari in June 2009, and the two were detained for nearly 1 year. Alkarama promoted their case as a human rights cause with the [[Working Group on Arbitrary Detention|UN Working Group on Arbitrary Detention]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://en.alkarama.org/qatar/387-qatar-abdullah-khowar-and-salem-al-kuwari-arbitrarily-detained-since-six-months|title=Qatar: Abdullah Khowar and Salem Al-Kuwari arbitrarily detained since six months|last=|first=|date=|work=Alkarama Foundation|access-date=2016-11-16|via=}}</ref> Apparently, shortly after Kuwari was released and permitted to return to his previous job at the Interior Ministry in Qatar.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/11156327/Al-Qaeda-terror-financier-worked-for-Qatari-government.html|title=Al-Qaeda terror financier worked for Qatari government|newspaper=Telegraph.co.uk|access-date=2016-11-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/world-leaders-1/pdfs/2010/June2010ChiefsDirectory.pdf|title=Chiefs of State & Cabinet Members of Foreign Governments|last=|first=|date=2016-06-01|website=Central Intelligence Agency (CIA)|publisher=|access-date=2016-11-16}}</ref> It is not clear what happened to Khawar at this time, but it can be assumed that he was released as well. In early 2011, the two were detained once again, and Alkarama advocated for the pair once more in [[Doha]] with the same UN group.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://en.alkarama.org/qatar/733-qatar-civil-servant-held-without-charge|title=Qatar: Civil servant held without charge|last=|first=|date=|work=Alkarama Foundation|access-date=2016-11-16|via=}}</ref> Before the UN group could take action, Khawar had been re-released. He attempted to leave Qatar, and at this time, [[Saudi Arabia]]n authorities soon arrested him.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://ar.alkarama.org/saudia/item/4149-2014-08-03-16-04-57|title=المملكة العربية السعودية: السيد عبد الله خوار، المواطن القطري معرض لخطر التعذيب|last=|first=|date=|work=|language=Arabic|access-date=2016-11-16|via=}}</ref> The U.N. group intervened, under the impression that he was arrested inhumanely for expressing his political views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ohchr.org/Documents/HRBodies/SP/A.HRC.18.51.pdf|title=Communications Report of Special Procedures|last=|first=|date=2011-09-05|website=United Nations Human Rights Office of the High Commissioner|publisher=United Nations General Assembly|access-date=2016-11-16}}</ref>

Though Khawar has had quite a few confrontations with law enforcement between the years of 2009 and 2011, but he has not been charged with any crime and still continues to function with an Iran-based al-Qaeda network, headed by [[Ezedin Abdel Aziz Khalil]]. Khalil operates as an al-Qaeda facilitator under an agreement between the terrorist group and the Iranian government.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.counterextremism.com/extremists/abdallah-ghanim-mafuz-muslim-al-khawar|title=Abdallah Ghanim Mafuz Muslim al-Khawar|last=|first=|date=|website=www.counterextremism.com|publisher=Counter Extremism Project|access-date=2016-11-16}}</ref> Khawar, however, still resides in Doha, despite the claims against him, and according to the country's Ministry of the Interior, he retains an active Qatari ID card and passport.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moi.gov.qa/site/eServices/services/indexE.html|title=MOI - eServices - Queries|website=www.moi.gov.qa|access-date=2016-11-16}}</ref>

