'''Joanna Simon''' is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[author]] and [[wine]] [[journalist]] known for her column in ''[[The Sunday Times]]''<ref name=jr-ww>{{cite web|last=Robinson |first= Jancis, jancisrobinson.com |title= Women and wine |url=http://www.jancisrobinson.com/articles/winenews0708 |date= July 7, 2004  }}</ref> for 22 years from 1987 to 2009,<ref name="deca-js">{{cite web|url=http://www.decanter.com/wine-news/joanna-simon-leaves-sunday-times-73460/|title=Joanna Simon leaves Sunday Times|last=Gibb|first=Rebecca, ''Decanter.com''|date=February 24, 2009}}</ref> where she was also a cookery writer from 2004 to 2009.  

She is founding editor of ''Waitrose Drinks'' magazine and writes for ''The World of Fine Wine'' and ''Decanter''. She is a wine taster for international competitions and presented BBC Radio 4’s series ''The Bottle Uncorked''. She has previously been wine and food editor of ''House & Garden'' and editor of both ''Wine'' and [[Wine & Spirit|''Wine & Spirit'']] magazines. 

Simon’s books include ''Discovering Wine'', ''Wine With Food'', ''The Sunday Times Book of Wine'', ''Wine: An Introduction'' and ''Harrods Book of Fine Wine''.

In September 2008 Simon was one of five UK wine writers, along with [[Tim Atkin|Tim Atkin MW]], [[Anthony Rose (wine)|Anthony Rose]], [[Tom Cannavan]] and [[Olly Smith]], to launch an online [[wine ratings]] magazine for the UK called The Wine Gang.

As a lecturer, she has urged [[Chilean wine]]makers to "'lighten up' on alcohol levels and the use of oak".<ref name="deca0908">{{cite web|last= Blanning |first=Beverly, MW  ''Decanter.com'' |title= 'Surprise' at Wines of Chile Awards |url= http://www.decanter.com/news/175156.html  |date= January 21, 2008 }}</ref>

She is married to the art historian and critic [[Robin_JH_Simon|Robin Simon]].

