{{Infobox politician | name = Willy Kruyt | image = KRUYT,_John_William.jpg | office = Member of the [[House of Representatives (Netherlands)|House of Representatives]]{{r|pp}} | term_start = 1918 | term_end = 1922 | birth_date = {{Birth date|1877|09|08}} | birth_place = [[Amsterdam]], [[Netherlands]] | death_date = Ca. July 1943{{r|blgnp}} | death_place = [[Berlin]], [[Nazi Germany]] | party = [[League of Christian Socialists]] | otherparty = Communist Party of Holland }} '''John William (Willy) Kruyt''' (1877–1943) was a Dutch Protestant minister and [[Christian socialism|Christian socialist]], later [[Communism|Communist]], politician.
==Background== The son of a Dutch publisher and his Scottish wife, Kruyt studied [[theology]] at Utrecht and joined the [[League of Christian Socialists]] in 1910.
==Early political career== In 1913, he was elected chairman of this party; in [[Dutch general election, 1918|1918]], he became its only member of the [[House of Representatives (Netherlands)|House of Representatives]]. In the same period, he worked as a [[Dutch Reformed Church|Reformed]] minister at [[Gennep]].{{r|blgnp}} When, in 1921, the League had disintegrated due to factional struggles between orthodox Protestants and [[Christian anarchism|anarchists]], Kruyt joined the [[Communist Party of the Netherlands|Communist Party]].{{r|pp}} He stood as a Communist candidate for the [[Dutch general election, 1922|1922 elections]], but was not re-elected.
==Later career== Following his wife's death, Kruyt emigrated to Berlin where he joined [[Workers International Relief]], then to Moscow in 1935 (presumably fleeing from the Nazis){{r|bwsa}} to work at the [[Russian State Library|Lenin State Library]]. Dissatisfied with [[Stalinism]], he trained as a [[espionage|spy]] in the hopes of getting back to the Netherlands this way. From England, he parachuted into Belgium in June 1942. He broke his leg and was arrested by the German occupiers who detained him at [[Fort Breendonk]].
==Death== Kruyt was tortured and deported to the [[Moabit]] prison in Berlin where he is thought to have been [[Execution by firing squad|executed by firing squad]] in 1943.{{r|bwsa}}
